                      Example: a simple objective function

Problem statement

  minimize
    sqrt((x - 1) ** 2 + (y - 1) ** 2)
  subject to
    sqrt(x ** 2 + y ** 2) >= 2
  with (x, y) bound to
    0 < x < 5
    0 < y < 5

Analytic solution

  Using the method of Lagrange multipliers the location of the minimum is
  revealed at (sqrt(2), sqrt(2)).

Examples

  1. simple.py  uses analytic gradient and jacobian information
  2. numeric.py uses numeric  gradient and jacobian 

